# Hero Screen — `NUI::CHeroScreen2`

Primary vtable **`0x00E79D3C`** belongs to **`NUI::CHeroScreen2`** (RTTI `.?AVCHeroScreen2@NUI@@` @ `0x00F39EC4`). This is the in-game hero screen widget (inventory, skills, biography, attributes panes). Not to be confused with AdvMap hero stats (`IHero` vtable `0x00E7E484` — see `.cursor/rules/h5x-re-hero-stats.mdc`).

## Object lifecycle

| Address | Role |
|---|---|
| `0x00AF7520` | **Factory** — `CCreateHeroScreen2`; `EngineAlloc(0x1B4)`, RTTI-casts arg to `NWorld::CRMVersionTracker`, calls ctor |
| `0x00AF7280` | **Ctor** — `CHeroScreen2(CHeroScreen2*, int)`; sets vtables, calls `0x0050F4C0` base init, then `0x00AF6FE0` |
| `0x00AF7C30` | **Alt ctor / subobject build** — same vtable layout without hero arg path |
| `0x00AF6FE0` | **Post-ctor init** — wires ref-counted UI children @ `[this+0xD4]`, `[this+0x174]`, `[this+0xDC]`, `[this+0x140]`, `[this+0x178]`, `[this+0x184]`, `[this+0x188]`, `[this+0x190]` |
| `0x00AF8310` | **Dtor helper** — tears down ref-counted fields |
| `0x00AF79A0` | **List cleanup** — drains circular list @ `[this+0xB0]` |

**Object size:** `0x1B4` bytes (factory alloc).

## Vtable map (multiple inheritance)

Constructors (`0x00AF7280` / `0x00AF7C30`) install four vptrs:

| Vptr location | Vtable | Vtordisp | Typical use |
|---|---|---|---|
| `[this+0x00]` | **`0x00E79D3C`** | — | **Primary** — screen logic, hero bind, tab merge |
| `[this+0x08]` | `0x00E79D2C` | — | Secondary interface (shared slots with combat stubs) |
| vb `@ [this+0x04]` → `[vb+4]` | `0x00E79D0C` | **`-0x198`** | MI base A |
| vb `@ [this+0x04]` → `[vb+8]` | **`0x00E79C9C`** | **`-0x1A8`** | **MI widget tree** — `FindChild`, pane visibility |

Virtual-base tables: `[this+0x04]` → `0x00E79EB4`, `[this+0x0C]` → `0x00E79EA8`, `[this+0x1B0]` → `0x00E19610`.

RTTI COL for primary vtable: `[vtable-4]` → `DAT_00EF768C`.

### Accessing the widget-tree MI subobject

Pattern used throughout hero-screen setup (`0x006CA4E0`, `0x006CA280`):

```asm
; ecx = CHeroScreen2* (primary this)
mov eax, [ecx+4]              ; vbptr
mov eax, [eax+8]              ; second vbase descriptor
lea edx, [eax+ecx+4]          ; MI this for vtable 0x00E79C9C
mov eax, [edx]                ; vtable
call [eax+0x94]               ; find_child_widget(...)
```

Pane layout builder `func_HeroScreen_BuildPanes` @ `0x006CA280` (patched by `HeroScreenUI.cpp` @ `0x006CA3F4`) calls `+0x94` on this MI interface to resolve `"Skills"`, `"Biography"`, `"Inventory"`, etc., then `+0x44` on child widgets to show/hide.

